title: Feds let go immigrants who commit crimes
text: TUCSON, Ariz. (AP) - The Yuma County Sheriff's Office says local authorities are footing the bill to prosecute immigrants who are arrested but who the federal government declines to charge. Capt. Eben Bratcher says Yuma authorities have jailed and prosecuted about 140 immigrants in the past year. They were arrested ... ...
